ygData.messageBody:
I don't know, but everny night when I'm on Fennin Ro, there are at
least 6 new players at the North Qeynos gate. I was also in West
Karana last night and ran across several players out there. When I
first created my character, it was sort of dead on the server, but it
seems to be picking up now.

--- In EverQuest@yahoogroups.com, "mlockridge01" <MLockridge01@c...>
wrote:
> I popped into West Commons my last two sessions to see if I could
bag
> a giant. Just wanted to come back to the zone and do that, since
now
> I can. The place is so empty! Back when I was a teen it was busy,
> laggy and fun. It is deserted now.
>
> I have to wonder, are there very few real noobs these days? Has POP
> changed the demographics in Norath? Places that were good fun and
> fellowship are dead. Even Velious is starting to seem empty. Are
all
> of the players getting into the high levels and now living in the
> Planes?
>
> Barto Proudfoot
